visionary comes along who should be honored for his Herculean
efforts in swimming upstream against the tide of political
correctness. Such a man is Frank Sodolak, who is pretty darned sure
he invented chicken-fried bacon. (Kelso, Austin American-Statesman)
MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   JEFFERSON-COLUMN _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Much has been made of
the almost unanimous support among blacks for President Clinton.
The most pious critics suggest that such support is an acceptance
of lower moral standards and a disregard for the level of decency
and integrity set forth in the Constitution. I suggest that such
critics consider another possibility: government-sanctioned social
conditioning. (Jefferson, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
