   FOOD-SOUP _ Chicken soup is a wonderful source of warmth during
the cold-hearted days of winter. (Heller, Dayton Daily News) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   FOOD-GOODSTUFF _ Food briefs: Experts say it's OK to eat the
rind on Brie. Plus, the reason homemade chicken stock may be better
than what you buy in a can. (Heller, Dayton Daily News). WITH
PHOTO. MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   DIETITIAN _ Questions on bakery muffins and rolls, soy milk for
kids, and how often one should weigh. (Austin American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   ENTERTAINMENT-ARTS
</P>
<P>
   JANIS _ Austin actress Andra Mitrovich wowed audiences with her
portrayal of Janis Joplin at Zach Scott Theater and now she's even
closer to the real thing by doing concerts with Janis' old band Big
Brother and the Holding Company. We talk to her and band members
about the eerie re-creation of the real thing. (Riemenschneider,
Austin American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   TVSURFER-COLUMN _ ATLANTA _ Quick interview with Clifton Powell
(Fox's ``South Central''), who on Sunday stars in ABC's
made-in-Georgia ``Selma, Lord, Selma'' as Martin Luther King Jr.
The film is based on Alabama's Bloody Sunday during '60s black
voter registration. On researching the role: ``I tried to get tapes
of him away from the crowd, just sitting with the SCLC or in the
back room meetings. I wanted to capture his natural voice, when he
wasn't doing a sermon.'' (Kloer, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
ETA: 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
