</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    A magical `Fair Lady'
 &HT;    By Eleanor Ringel
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Audrey Hepburn made two movies with her first husband, Mel
Ferrer (``War and Peace'' and ``Green Mansions''). Best skip them
and, instead, savor the on-screen magic between her and Rex
Harrison in ``My Fair Lady.'' This beautifully restored DVD version
of the acclaimed Oscar-winning musical looks wonderful, as you
might expect, but it also offers some enticing bonuses. Such as
commentary by art director Gene Allen and by singer Marni Nixon
(she subbed for Hepburn on the songs as she had done for Natalie
Wood in ``West Side Story''). Plus, for those really into this
movie and/or the ever-fair Hepburn, you can hear her versions of
the songs ``Show Me'' and ``Wouldn't It Be Loverly?''
</P>
<P>
   Eleanor Ringel writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
