<HEADLINE>
WRESTING STAR SHAWN MICHAELS RECOVERING FROM SURGERY 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 By CARMINA DANINI  
 c.1999 San Antonio Express-News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN ANTONIO _ World Wrestling Federation superstar Shawn
Michaels is recovering from back surgery at a San Antonio hospital.
</P>
<P>
   Surgeons fused the wrestler's fourth and fifth vertebrae, said
Clyde McCormick, Michaels' attorney.
</P>
<P>
   ``It was very difficult and it took a lot longer than we
expected, but he's doing very well,'' said Pablo Vasquez, one of
the physicians who operated on Michaels.
</P>
<P>
   The popular wrestler was resting comfortably after four hours of
surgery on Tuesday and will probably leave the hospital this
weekend, Vasquez said.
</P>
<P>
   Michaels, 33, known as ``The Heartbreak Kid,'' suffered a
serious back injury last year when The Undertaker tossed him
through a table during a match.
</P>
<P>
   He won the WWF's championship in 1996, and lost it a few months
later to Sycho Sid after Sid decked him with a television camera.
</P>
<P>
   To the delight of his fans, Michaels regained the championship
in January 1997 after a grueling, 17-minute grudge match at the
Alamodome.
</P>
<P>
   Last week, Michaels announced his retirement but said he would
continue to work as a WWF commissioner and with community groups.
</P>
<P>
   He also says he plans to open a wrestling school in San Antonio.
</P>
<P>
   Vasquez said any return to the ring by Michaels would put too
much pressure on his spinal column.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
