<P>
   NATIONAL NEWS (``a'' category)
</P>
<P>
   UNABOMBER-FUND (Albany, N.Y.) _ In an effort to avoid a
potentially huge tax bill, David Kaczynski says he will establish a
special victims fund with $535,000 of the $1 million he received
for turning in his brother, convicted Unabomber Theodore Kaczynski.
By JAY JOCHNOWITZ.
</P>
<P>
   POLICE-KILLING (Oakland, Calif.) _ The young man accused of
killing a police officer may be a sad legacy of the Jonestown
massacre, says his mother and a psychiatrist who worked with
survivors of the Peoples Temple cult. By GREGORY LEWIS.
</P>
<P>
   CALIF-EDUCATION (Sacramento, Calif.) _ Lawmakers and lobbyists
listening to Gov. Gray Davis lately are finding that several
education proposals he made during the campaign somehow have
vanished. Depending on who is talking, the proposed overhauls were
killed or rewritten either because of pressure from the powerful
teachers union, a lack of money or other reasons. By ROBERT
SALLADAY.
</P>
