   BUSINESS/FINANCIAL NEWS (``f'' category)
</P>
<P>
   BANK-AMERICA-MINORITIES (San Francisco) _ The $70 billion the
Bank of America proposes to make available in California for loans
in low- or moderate-income communities and to minorities is ``a
floor, not a ceiling,'' and the pot will surely grow, the bank's
chairman says. By GEORGE RAINE.
</P>
<P>
   FOOD (``d'' category)
</P>
<P>
   HAZELNUTS (Albany, N.Y.) _ The flavor of hazelnuts seems to be
in everything, from coffee to ice cream, yet you could count
America's per capita consumption of these little heart-shaped nuts
on one hand. Actually, on two fingers. That's right, for all its
popularity, Americans only eat two hazelnuts per person, per year
according to the Hazelnut Marketing Board. By RUTH FANTASIA.
</P>
<P>
   SPORTS (``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   WWF-MICHAELS (San Antonio) _ World Wrestling Federation
superstar Shawn Michaels is recovering from back surgery at a San
Antonio hospital. Michaels, 33, known as ``The Heartbreak Kid,''
suffered a serious back injury last year during a match. By CARMINA
DANINI.
</P>
<P>
   BKN-JORDAN (San Francisco) _ Michael Jordan's re-retirement has
forced us to examine our attitude toward one of America's most
prevalent contemporary pastimes _ slapping his best highlights into
a single reel, backed by music you would throw your radio out the
window to avoid hearing ever again. By RAY RATTO.
</P>
<P>
   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MORSE-COLUMN (San Francisco) _ Someday archaeologists will dig
up heaps of old newspapers and conclude that San Francisco was a
city obsessed _ not with sex, not with beauty or style, not with
food or restaurants, not even with itself _ but with ballparks. By
ROB MORSE.
</P>
