<HEADLINE>
COOKING CLASS IS IN SESSION 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By JUDY WALKER  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
PHOENIX - Welcome to Cooking 201, ``The Arizona Republic'' food!
section's new series of lessons on cooking topics. 
The lessons start today with yeast breads. We will feature one
topic a month, throughout the year, for a total of 12 classes.
Topics will be a bit more sophisticated than those in last year's
series, Cooking 101, in which thousands of readers and students
participated. 
If you want to review any of Cooking 101's 20 lessons in the basics
of cookery, they are available on the World Wide Web at the
newspaper's Web site at www.azcentral.com/food. 
Recommended texts for advanced reading: ``CookWise, The Hows &AMP; Whys
of Successful Cooking,'' by Shirley O. Corriher (Morrow, $28.50),
<TEXT>
<P>
   and ``On Food &AMP; Cooking: The Science and Lore of the Kitchen,''
by Harold McGee (Fireside, $21 paperback). &QL; 
Next month: Cake decorating. &QL;
</P>
