<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-UNION-LIST-$QDV17-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    MANY SPEECH PROPOSALS HAVE LEAKED IN ADVANCE
 &HT;    With UNION. For release Sunday, Jan. 17.
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ Many proposals that President Clinton is expected
to make in his Tuesday address have been announced or leaked to
news organizations in advance. They include:
</P>
<P>
   _ A budget request for $100 billion over six years to beef up
military readiness.
</P>
<P>
   _ A $1.4 billion, five-year program to let people aged 55 to 64
purchase Medicare health insurance coverage.
</P>
<P>
   _ A $6.2 billion, five-year package of tax cuts and other help
for families giving long-term care to the elderly and disabled.
</P>
<P>
   _ A plan to spend up to $1 billion a year to preserve open space
through federal land purchases and federal conservation grants to
states and localities.
</P>
<P>
   _ $215 million to test and treat inmates for drug use to keep
them from returning to crime once freed.
</P>
<P>
   _ A sharp increase in funds for after-school programs.
</P>
<P>
   _ A set of programs aimed at helping mid-career U.S. workers
make the transition into high-tech jobs.
</P>
<P>
   ENDIT
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
