A1436 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r e &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-TALKING-RADIO-LADN     01-13 0319
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TALKING-RADIO-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
JACKSON CAN BE SEEN AND HEARD AT THE MUSEUM
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By FRED SHUSTER 
c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ &UR;  &LR; Michael Jackson, who recently returned to the
airwaves at talk radio KRLA-AM (1110), is broadcasting through the
end of next month from the Museum of Television &AMP; Radio in Beverly
Hills.
</P>
<P>
   And you're invited to watch.
</P>
<P>
   Jackson's news-talk program is originating from the museum's
glass-enclosed high-tech studio; listeners can drop by anytime
between 9 a.m. and noon weekdays.
</P>
<P>
   Comic George Carlin, a recent visitor to Jackson's show, took a
look around and joked that the veteran broadcaster must be feeling
a bit like a museum piece.
</P>
<P>
   ``The first day, Larry King was walking by the museum and we
happened to see him and invited him in,'' Jackson said Tuesday. ``I
want to make this the radio station of record for L.A. and I can't
think of a more seductive setting. This gives me the opportunity to
meet groups of students _ I've had fourth-, eighth- and
10th-graders in. And by far the best were the fourth-graders, every
single one of whom knew what they wanted to be when they grew up.''
</P>
<P>
   Jackson, who spent three decades at talk outlet KABC-AM (790),
said he also expected to use the museum's auditorium at some point
for a Town Hall broadcast.
</P>
<P>
   The Museum of Television &AMP; Radio is at 465 N. Beverly Drive,
Beverly Hills. Information: (310) 786-1000.
</P>
<P>
   HERE AND THERE: Radio vet Johnny Magnus will host afternoons on
adult standards KLAC-AM (570), starting Jan. 25. Magnus previously
worked at KMPC-AM, KIQQ-FM, KJOI-AM and most recently spearheaded
the ``Music of Your Life'' format for syndication. ... KLOS-FM
(95.5) music director Rita Wilde has been named program director at
the ABC-owned rock station. As a result of the promotion, she has
given up her midday air shift. &QL; 
ENDIT &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
