<SLUG> BC-ROSENFELD-SHORTTAKES14-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    SHORTTAKES: Something to impeach over
 &HT;    By Arnold Rosenfeld
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   If you think the Monica Lewinsky matter merits impeachment, take
a look at the increasingly dippy UNSCOM spy scandal as something
more like a real reason to throw a president out of office.
</P>
<P>
   Let's say it's true the CIA planted a bug on U.N. weapons
inspectors in Iraq. Let's say the CIA ran the plan past Bill
Clinton beforehand. Let's also imagine the CIA didn't.
</P>
<P>
   Playing fast and loose with UNSCOM, in effect ending inspections
and allowing Saddam Hussein to continue to cook bio-chemicals, is
closer to the kind of abuse the framers had in mind when they made
high crimes and misdemeanors the standard for impeachment.
</P>
<P>
   Did Bill Clinton know? I have no earthly idea. Was he kept in
the dark? Ditto. Nobody's asking. One can only presume U.N.
inspectors have no sex life worth worrying about.
</P>
<P>
   Arnold Rosenfeld is editor-in-chief of the Cox Newspapers.
E-mail: arnold.rosenfeld(at)cox.com.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
