<HEADLINE>
PLEASE PASS THE BREAD . . . COOKBOOKS 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By JUDY WALKER  
 c.1999 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   PHOENIX - Other resources, besides the bread sections in
``CookWise'' and ``On Food and Cooking'': &QL; 
 &QL; 
Handmade breads, artisan and otherwise &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``Amy's Bread,'' by Amy Scherber (William Morrow and Co., $23).
</P>
<P>
   ``American's Bread Book: 300 Authentic Recipes for America's
Favorite Homemade Breads,'' by Mary Gubser (Quill, $14).
</P>
<P>
   ``Bernard Clayton's Complete Book of Breads,'' by Bernard
Clayton Jr. (Simon &AMP; Schuster, $30).
</P>
<P>
   ``Nancy Silverton's Breads from the La Brea Bakery: Recipes for
the
</P>
<P>
   Connoisseur,'' by Nancy Silverton, Laurie Ochoa and Ruth Reichl
(Villard Books, $30).
</P>
<P>
   ``The Wooden Spoon Book of Bread: The Secrets of Successful
Baking,'' by Marilyn M. Moore (Atlantic Monthly Press, $15). &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   For bread machines &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``Electric Bread'' and ``More Electric Bread'' (Innovative
Cooking Enterprises, $29).
</P>
<P>
   ``Bread Machine Magic'' and ``More Bread Machine Magic,'' by
Linda Rehberg and Lois Conway (St. Martin's Griffin, $11.95).
</P>
<P>
   ``Rustic European Breads from Your Bread Machine,'' by Linda
West Eckhart and Diana Collingwood Butts (Doubleday, $27.50). &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   For food processors &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``The Best Bread Ever: Great Homemade Bread Using Your Food
</P>
<P>
   Processor,'' by Charles Van Over and Priscilla Martel (Broadway
Books, $27.50). &QL;
</P>
