<P>
   THOMPSON-COLUMN (Washington) _ ``Bipartisan'' is the word
senators are using as they stride before TV cameras to describe the
manner in which they and their colleagues are conducting the
impeachment trial of Bill Clinton. But the routine often is nothing
more than a charade to please the folks back home. Most senators
know how they will vote on impeachment. By ROBERT E. THOMPSON.
</P>
