antitrust trial against Microsoft Corp. (Glass, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   Moving in (w) Washington and (f) financial categories.
</P>
<P>
   LUCENT _ Since its spinoff from AT&AMP;T two years ago, Lucent has
grown into a domineering force in the technology industry, and
increasingly is making its mark locally. (Holsendolph, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   PORTMAN _ A federal lawsuit filed by two former female
executives at Portman Properties alleges that John Portman harassed
women employees and encouraged a pervasive atmosphere of sexual
intimidation at the company. (Salter, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   BIZMAGS _ What the business magazines are reporting. (Walker,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   BRAZIL-DEVALUE _ The impact of Brazil's decision to accelerate
the devaluation of its currency on Georgia companies that do
extensive business in Latin America. (Quinn, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   CAPSTAR - AUSTIN _Only one Austin area company went public in
1998, although several failed. We take a look at how Capstar
Broadcasting has done since its IPO last May. with feverline of
stock price. (Golz, Austin American-Statesman)
</P>
<P>
   RAIL-OIL _ AUSTIN _In one of the most substative moves by the
state to help Texas oil producers, the Texas Railroad Commission is
pushing legislation that would give oil companies tax breaks as
long as prices stay at rock-bottom lows. (Hight, Austin
American-Statesman)
</P>
<P>
   SYNTELLECT _ In a windowless office near Cumberland Mall, 203
workers stand shoulder to shoulder, handling up to 50 million
customer calls a year. On a good day, about three of these workers
are carbon based. The others are computers. ``I like to say that we
run this operation through 5,000 silicon-based agents, not
carbon-based (human) ones,'' jokes J. Lawrence Bradner, a longtime
Scientific-Atlanta executive, now chairman of Syntellect. (Haddad,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   ATSTUPID _ An update on Stupid PC of Norcross, which recently
rolled out a big expansion, adding retail sites in five cities. It
added an internet retail site and struck a deal with IBM that lets
it sell computers to the business market. Stupid PC has been known
in its short life as a down-home, high-tech retailer. (Clothier,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   Y2K-TESTS _ Most PC software programs that test for Y2K problems
conduct limited searches, exploring only the computer's first two
layers - its real-time clock and its BIOS, a chip in which basic
instructions have been hardwired. But operating systems such as
Windows or UNIX are the levels on which most problems will occur,
and that's where Alpharetta-based Client/Server Technologies enters
the picture. (Chambers, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
