   BKN-JORDAN-TIMELINE _ DAYTON _ Prepared by Patrick Foose.
</P>
<P>
   BKN-JORDAN-HAWKS _ ATLANTA _ The Hawks plan to play pick-up
games in the morning at Georgia Tech, then go watch Jordan's news
conference on TV. (Denberg, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   BOXING
</P>
<P>
   BOX-TYSON-ADVANCE _ LAS VEGAS _ Mike Tyson returns to the ring
Saturday for the first fight since he turned cannibal against
Evander Holyfield. Both a fight will be 19 months after
Holyfield-Tyson II. Few doubt Tyson is back for money, that his
``love'' for the sport has long since dissipated. But he has
changed his entire camp, including getting rid of promoter Don
King. (Schultz, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 30.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   BOX-ARCHDEACON-COLUMN _ LAS VEGAS _ He has studied the films of
several Mike Tyson fights, especially the last one against Evander
Holyfield, the one that got him banned from boxing. That means he's
been left with that image of an enraged, animalistic Tyson, turning
his head from the bloodied Holyfield and spitting a gristly piece
of the champion's right ear onto the ring canvas. ``They gave me
some earmuffs, but I don't think I'll need them.'' a laughing
Francois Botha said Tuesday, four days before he meets the
reinstated Tyson in a 10-round bout at the MGM Grand Garden in Las
Vegas. (Archdeacon, Dayton Daily News) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   FOOTBALL
</P>
<P>
   NFL PLAYOFFS
</P>
<P>
   FBN-FALCONS _ ATLANTA _ Some cities are fortunate if they ever
experience sports magic with their professional teams, where their
teams take their places among the elite. When the Braves made their
worst-to-first run in 1991, it took a shocked state of Georgia by
surprise. You hate to utter the S-word (Super Bowl) now, but the
Falcons run is beginning to look a lot like the Braves' march in
'91, and the city and state are responding. (Stinson, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 25.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   FBN-FALCONS-EDGE _ ATLANTA _ Analysis on who has the edge
between Falcons passing game and Vikings pass defense.
(Pasquarelli, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 20. WITH CHART.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-VIKINGS-GREEN _ MINNEAPOLIS _ To say coach Dennis Green was
under fire in Minnesota is an understatement. He disenfrachised
himself from fans and owners with the publication of his
controversial book, then complicated matters by making some
outlandish public statements. This was supposed to be the year
Green ran himself out of town, but his team hasn't let that happen.
Winning cures all ills. (Bunn, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 25.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-VIKINGS-RAIL _ MINNEAPOLIS _ Vikings notebook. (Bunn,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   FBN-FALCONS-NOTES _ ATLANTA _ Falcons notebook. (Winklejohn,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   FBN-FALCONS-NEWS ATLANTA _ News story from Falcons. (Winklejohn,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 12.
</P>
<P>
   FBN-VIKINGS-RANDLE _ MINNEAPOLIS _ When he takes the field on
Sunday, Vikings defensive lineman John Randle will look a lot like
a WCW wrestler, face paint and the works. Randle is perhaps the
biggest trash-talker in football, but he backs his brashness with
strong performances. (Bunn, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
