u w &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-IMPEACH-COLLECTIBLES-     01-13 0789
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-IMPEACH-COLLECTIBLES-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
AS TRIAL BEGINS, COLLECTORS SCOUR FOR A PIECE OF HISTORY 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 By ERIC ROSENBERG  
 c.1999 Hearst Newspapers  
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ With the Senate trial of President Clinton getting
under way Thursday, memorabilia collectors are scouring for
keepsakes in the first impeachment trial of a president in 131
years.
</P>
<P>
   Serious collectors already are bombarding dealers with requests
to purchase the tickets that will be handed out each day to members
of the public viewing the proceedings.
</P>
<P>
