the lies to the American people. Those acts, even many of President
Clinton's harshest critics say, are not impeachable offenses.
Instead, the case for impeachment is a winding legal staircase, one
that must be understood step by step, according to those who
believe that Clinton's actions must lead to his removal. By Michael
Kranish. 1650 words.
