   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 BC-ADD-BUDGET-AZR 
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients) 
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The following Arizona Republic story has been added for use by
clients of the NYTimes News Service for Thursday, Jan. 14. If you
have any questions, please contact the Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
</P>
<P>
   MONTINI-COLUMN (Phoenix) -Joe Arpaio, the ''toughest sheriff in
America,'' is cheerful. He's relaxed. He's talking to me about the
$8.2 million that Maricopa County will pay to the family of a man
killed in his jail, and he's at peace. Happy. And he should be. He
won. By E.J. MONTINI Story will move in the ``A'' and ``K''
categories. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
