<TEXT>
<P>
   Here are the business news stories the Los Angeles Daily News
plans to move for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs
of Thursday, Jan. 14, and thereafter. The stories will carry the
``f'' financial news category code unless otherwise noted. For
questions about stories, contact David Brady at the Daily News,
(818) 713-3470.
</P>
<P>
   WARNER-WEB (Los Angeles) _ Warner Bros. announces an Internet
venture with FortuneCity.com. The ACMEcity.com site _ a joint
venture that takes its name from a mythical company in Warner Bros.
cartoon lore _ will place all of Warner's key properties onto a
single location on the Web. By Dave McNary.
</P>
<P>
   CASINO-EXPANSION (Los Angeles) _ North Hollywood, Calif.-based
Landmark Entertainment, which specializes in theme park rides, will
design a $120 million expansion at the Barona Indian Reservation
casino in San Diego County, including doubling the size of the
casino and adding a two-story carousel, bingo and off-track
wagering areas. By Dave McNary.
</P>
