response to another dose of emerging market turmoil. Brazil's plan
to effectively devalue its currency initially deflated the
confidence of stock investors in the United States and abroad. But
after a sharp selloff in the first half hour of trading, American
stock prices rebounded steadily throughout the day. By Edward
Wyatt.
