prepared to absorb the shock. In contrast to the aftermath of
Russia's collapse in August, the initial flight to safety that
followed the Brazilian currency devaluation Wednesday did not turn
to panic in American stock and bond markets. Big bettors learned
their lesson: Fool me once, shame on you. Fool me twice, shame on
me. By Jonathan Fuerbringer.
