<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-VIKINGS-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
WEATHER MAY BE COLD, BUT VIKINGS KNOW THEY ARE RED HOT  
(RK)
</HEADLINE>
   By   JACK CURRY   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   EDEN PRAIRIE, Minn. _ Randy Moss had to travel about 30 feet to
get from the Vikings' locker room to his sports utility vehicle
Wednesday, yet he still sprinted as if he were running a fly
pattern at the Metrodome. A temperature of minus 4 will cause that
sort of hurried behavior, even to someone as smooth as Moss.
</P>
<P>
   When Moss returned to the warmth of the indoors, he regained his
swagger. The rookie wide receiver sounded cool and looked
confident. So did all of the Vikings. They did not sound arrogant
or look antsy. They simply seemed intent on vanquishing the Atlanta
Falcons in the National Football Conference championship game on
Sunday so they can soar into the Super Bowl.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's about who wants it more and who's going to be hungry
enough to make it happen,'' said Moss. ``We've got a goal. Just
win.''
</P>
<P>
   It was a recurring theme from the Vikings inside a weight room
that served as a temporary setting for some news conferences. The
Vikings were polite while discussing the Falcons, repeatedly
calling them the best team they have opposed all season. But the
fearsome Vikings, who set a National Football League record by
scoring 556 points in the regular season, surely expect to score on
Atlanta and surely believe their dream season will continue.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's beyond the point of trying to prove anything,'' said
Robert Smith, a running back. ``You lose, you're out. We're not
trying to get any more people on the bandwagon. We're trying to get
to the Super Bowl.''
</P>
<P>
   Moss added, ``We got two games, hopefully two games, to show how
explosive we are.''
</P>
<P>
   Additional evidence is unnecessary. Randall Cunningham
resurrected his career with 34 touchdown passes and the highest
rating of any quarterback in football. Moss abused defensive backs
while corralling 17 touchdown passes and is likely to be the rookie
of the year, Chris Carter snatched a dozen touchdown passes and
Smith rushed for 1,187 yards. With an attack that is talented and
unpredictable behind Brian Billick, the clever offensive
coordinator, the Vikings are difficult to defend against.
</P>
<P>
   How would Moss contain himself if he was reincarnated as a
defensive back?
</P>
<P>
   ``I think the way to stop me is slowing me down by jacking me in
the mouth,'' said Moss. ``But I think that's hard to do once I get
focused.''
</P>
<P>
   Smith chuckled and added, ``I'm glad it's not my job to stop
us.''
</P>
<P>
   How relaxed were the Vikings five days before they will compete
for a trip to the Super Bowl? Cunningham looked as if he just
awakened from a nap as he discussed ``the peace inside'' him as he
awaits the biggest game of his career, Carter juked around some
weight machines before his interview and Moss actually said that
Atlanta's Jamal Anderson is his favorite running back in football.
The smooth Moss was in from the cold, on this day and obviously in
this glorious season. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-01-13-99 1954EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
