<P>
   QUAKE-PEOPLE (Los Angeles) _ After the jolts from the Northridge
Earthquake tossed an armoir onto Susie Riley and broke her neck,
doctors stared at the ground and dodged questions when she asked if
she would walk again. Like so many victims of the 1994 temblor, the
Valencia woman spent months in the hospital fighting to reclaim her
life. And like many, her story is one of redemption and resiliance.
By Phillip Browne. (Will move in the ``a'' national and ``n''
California news files.)
