<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR THURSDAY, JANUARY 14
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Thursday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-SAFRICA-MURAL-NYT (moved on Monday, Jan. 11)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, Jan. 11,
about a mural in Johannesburg that is a testament to the role
played by theater people in the anti-apartheid struggle in South
Africa misattributed the play ``Woza Albert.'' It was written by
Mbongeni Ngema, Percy Mtwa and Barney Simon, not by Athol Fugard,
who is pictured in the mural.
</P>
<P>
   BC-CRANE-COLTEC-NYT (moved on Sunday, Jan. 10)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Sunday, Jan. 10,
about Crane Company's lawsuit to force Coltec Industries to
consider its takeover offer misstated the reason Crane's proposal
would be tax-free. In such proposals, the acquirer uses its common
stock to purchase the target company's common stock, a transaction
that is considered nontaxable. While the combined value of the
companies' balance sheets helps determine how the acquirer will
report earnings, it is not a factor in whether the transaction is
taxable.
</P>
</TEXT>
