<HEADLINE>
QUOTATION OF THE DAY
</HEADLINE>
 (Eds.: This quotation refers to BC-BREAST-CANCER-NYT, which moved
in ``a'' news file.) 
c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``I knew growing up, my whole life, that women in my family got
breast cancer and died. It was not a question of, will I get it? It
was a question of when.''
</P>
<P>
   _STACI MISHKIN, who had both breasts removed to protect herself
from breast cancer.
</P>
</TEXT>
